Vendored Kronos model code
==========================

Source : https://github.com/shiyu-coder/Kronos  (model/kronos.py, model/module.py)
License: MIT (c) the Kronos authors
Paper  : "Kronos: A Foundation Model for the Language of Financial Markets", arXiv:2508.02739

Only the model definition is vendored here (no PyPI package exists). Local
modifications to kronos.py:
  1. Import header: the `sys.path` hack and `from model.module import *` were
     replaced with a relative `from .module import *` so it works as a package.
  2. A `sample_logits` flag was threaded through auto_regressive_inference /
     generate / predict / predict_batch (default True) so callers can request
     deterministic greedy decoding (sample_logits=False).
Pre-trained weights are downloaded from the Hugging Face Hub (NeoQuasar/*) at
runtime by app.ml.kronos_loader.
